HEADWORD: Whitebeam
<hw>White"beam`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The common beam tree of England (<spn>Pyrus Aria</spn>); -- so
called from the white, woolly under surface of the leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

